	<td bgcolor="#666699" width="100%" valign="top">
	
	<!-- Main Post Body -->
	<table width="100%" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0" border="0">
	<td bgcolor="#4D4D73"><img src="images/posticon.gif" border="0" alt="Old Post"></td><td width="100%" bgcolor="#4D4D73"><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
	Posted 12-12-2003 <font color="#FEDE01">07:53 PM</font></font></td>
	</tr>
	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">I'm not rich.  I've got all sandblasted gear, with a couple of nice pieces added recently by my guildies.  I've got about 3k in the bank.  I play with my g/f all the time I can when I play, because we enjoy playing the game together.  <br />
<br />
Recently, we decided to pool our money until I can afford a horse.  Then we'll pool our money until we can afford Blessed full Mithril for her (she's a paladin)<br />
<br />
Well, we all know that in pickup groups, unless someone is thoughtful, or you jump straight to the forefront, a lot of hte time the melees get a large share of the PP, because of the way autosplit works.<br />
<br />
I'm fine with this, and I either patiently hope for someone to give me loot, or I accept I get nothing, or I get up in mobs faces for the last 10th of the healthbar and loot it before it hits the ground.<br />
<br />
Most of the time, pickup groups are okay with this.  In fact, since so many twinks come through DL, where I am currently grinding, a lot of people don't want the paltry plat that comes from looting DL monsters (about 100-200pp in pp and gp, and drops that might double that, in a 3-4 hour session)<br />
<br />
Well, last night, I was grouped with a wizard who thought she needed all the loot.  Everytime anyone else looted a corpse, she called them a ninja looter, or complained that she never got any pp from the mobs because she was always finishing them off with nukes.<br />
<br />
I was medding hard, so my g/f was looting, about as often as the other 3 melees in the group, and trying to let the wizardess get in.  As a result, the plat was being split 5 ways mostly, with me getting the tails of auto-split.<br />
<br />
Well then the wizardess sends a tell to my g/f and says since we have the same last name we must be 2 boxed and the same person, and that we need to give her half of what we have because we don't deserve a full share.  We politely responded that we're not two boxed, that we're seperate people, and that we already are going to deal with a diminished share because Moonsorrow was not looting.<br />
<br />
At which point she started berating us with tells about how she was poor, and had to support her 65 cleric husbands 'dot use, and that she had jsut used the last of her 30k savings on getting her int up to 242 so she needed plat more than I did.<br />
<br />
She was riding on at least a 30k drogmor, as well.<br />
<br />
I've never even seen 30k all in one place at one time.  And it hurt my feelings that she felt that I deserved a half share of my platinum for my hard work in keeping the group alive.  And it made me angry that she thought because she couldn't find some way to max her int with 5x the amount of money that me and my g/f have between the two of us, that we needed to give her more than her share.<br />
<br />
I know I had plenty of options, as far as leaving the group (we were the MT and the healer... losing the wizard wouldn't have ended our session by any means), and I know that she might not deserve as much thought and time as I put into this post.<br />
<br />
But I needed a rant.  Darnit.  I'm working on my PP just like everyone else at my level.  I've never told someone that I deserve more than they do.  I've certainly never accused 2 people in the group of being 2 boxed and thus *cheating* the group out of cash.<br />
<br />
I want a pony.</font></p>
	
	<p><p><img src="/forums/images/sig_separator.gif" width="282" height="11" Alt="Hey! Watch where you point that thing!"><br>
<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">

Moonsorrow Nocturne<br />
High Elven Cleric of Tunare<br />
51st Circle<br />
Guild Member of Anzac<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=844125" target="_blank">My Shiny Armor</a>
</font></p></p>
