	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">Autosplit is annoying.  I hate the fact that it "realistically" divides up coins.<br />
<br />
Which means if a group of 6 finds a critter with 5 pp, 11gp, 65sp, and 12cp that the one who loots and is autosplitting gets<br />
<br />
5pp, 6gp, 15sp and 2cp<br />
<br />
and everyone else gets<br />
1gp, 10sp, and 2cp<br />
<br />
5.752 versus 0.202 or about 28 times as much cash. in an adverse scenario like this, but always guaranteed the largest share.<br />
<br />
Part of me wishes /autosplit would work 'magically' and divide up the coins as if the whole load was as perfect as possible, meaning that the 6.762pp found on the critter would become 1pp 1gp 2sp 7cp for the whole party.<br />
<br />
Though Hannorel is right, if I want a fair split guaranteed, I should do LDoN.  For some reason folks on my server 'prefer' to have the Cleric ML on LDoN, which means I can be sure I do a fair split.<br />
<br />
Also wanted to address a couple other comments:<br />
<br />
Re: Avoiding PC, HHK, OT, and DL<br />
<br />
You're so right.  And if I hadn't been trying to get plane-enabled, I wouldn't have XP'd in those zones.  Now that I can join my guild on most raids, I'm going to be looking for fun zones to group in, rather than making sure I'm in a group from the moment I log on until the moment I ding.  DL experience and loot overall treated me very well (I've gotten into groups with twinks where *no one* wants a split of the treasure... to them it's barely worth carrying the 400pp in items and cash back to PoK)<br />
<br />
But you're right, for meeting good players, those zones haven't been perfect.<br />
<br />
Re: Wizard being selfish and not grouping with her again.<br />
<br />
You're right, but I have a natural nice bent that has caused me to group with people I dislike just because "they were in the group before me" or "I don't want to be a primadonna, telling the group to get rid of the wizard or I'll leave"<br />
<br />
Heh, the other thing about this wizard is she only nuked when the critter was near full health.  I guess she wanted to get the most mileage out of her nukes.<br />
<br />
What she mostly got is aggro.  Then she ran all around the zone on her fast droggy, while the mob beat her around.  We tried to get her to stand still... but she kept telling us it was part of her "strategy"<br />
<br />
Finally 2 in a row got her.  It was a nice way to call it a night ::cackle::</font></p>
	
	<p></p>
